WEBVTT

00:00:10.755 --> 00:00:12.325
Aside from your father's case,

00:00:12.875 --> 00:00:15.915
Phakphum is known to be clean
and out of any shady business.

00:00:16.875 --> 00:00:20.365
Maybe there’s more to this than we know.

00:00:20.835 --> 00:00:23.045
the motive is brought to court,

00:00:23.955 --> 00:00:26.245
it will damage your past reputation.

00:00:27.115 --> 00:00:29.605
You should watch your back, Phakphum.

00:00:29.795 --> 00:00:31.925
As a former colleague,

00:00:32.355 --> 00:00:33.845
I'm genuinely concerned.

00:00:34.035 --> 00:00:36.845
Maybe P'Ann didn't
commit suicide after all.

00:00:36.875 --> 00:00:38.605
If Bowontat is truly dangerous,

00:00:38.635 --> 00:00:40.525
then you and Vicky need to be careful.

00:00:45.675 --> 00:00:47.125
Phakphum is such a strange one.

00:00:47.955 --> 00:00:49.925
In critical condition at the hospital.

00:00:50.995 --> 00:00:52.045
But hides it from his child.

00:00:54.995 --> 00:00:56.645
The sacrificial father figure.

00:00:57.555 --> 00:00:59.491
Afraid it'll break her heart.

00:01:00.155 --> 00:01:01.805
But he failed to teach her
how to survive the real world.

00:01:02.635 --> 00:01:06.485
Raising her like that
made her submissive and naive.

00:01:07.235 --> 00:01:08.565
But come to think of it.

00:01:08.915 --> 00:01:11.525
She’s actually perfect
for a daughter-in-law.

00:01:23.315 --> 00:01:23.845
Yeah.

00:01:24.955 --> 00:01:26.245
Come to think of it,

00:01:27.115 --> 00:01:29.165
I do feel a bit sorry about that Dr. Anya.

00:01:30.755 --> 00:01:31.965
Now that she's gone,

00:01:32.875 --> 00:01:35.216
The flow of information
on Phakphum has hit a snag.

00:01:36.715 --> 00:01:37.565
Sigh.

00:01:37.835 --> 00:01:40.205
Who knows where he's
hiding to recover right now.

00:01:44.275 --> 00:01:44.765
Damn.

00:01:46.035 --> 00:01:46.405
Oh?

00:01:56.635 --> 00:01:57.845
Hey there, Captain.

00:01:58.355 --> 00:01:59.685
Are you asleep yet?

00:02:00.355 --> 00:02:03.349
Sorry for texting you so late.

00:02:04.955 --> 00:02:06.245
I usually stay up late anyway.

00:02:06.995 --> 00:02:08.365
Even if I were already asleep,

00:02:08.595 --> 00:02:12.113
If it's you calling, I’d be more
than happy to wake up and answer.

00:02:12.675 --> 00:02:13.605
Umm...

00:02:14.435 --> 00:02:16.285
Anyway, is there anything I can do for you, Captain?

00:02:19.115 --> 00:02:19.953
Whoa.

00:02:20.395 --> 00:02:21.885
Why would you say something like that?

00:02:26.675 --> 00:02:29.125
The company that’s been buying up
all the land in your old neighborhood is

00:02:29.275 --> 00:02:30.685
Billionaire Property.

00:02:31.795 --> 00:02:33.065
Do you know who the original owner was?

00:02:34.115 --> 00:02:36.256
Thaddao Mahasapkijboriboon.

00:02:39.835 --> 00:02:41.005
She’s Burin’s wife.

00:02:41.475 --> 00:02:42.965
But they aren't legally married.

00:02:43.675 --> 00:02:45.553
And back when Burin was in politics,

00:02:46.795 --> 00:02:48.965
He transferred various
shares to his wife's relatives,

00:02:49.235 --> 00:02:50.685
And sold some to foreign investors.

00:02:51.635 --> 00:02:53.085
For the past 20 years,

00:02:53.835 --> 00:02:56.611
They’ve been laundering and
moving assets around like it’s a game.

00:02:57.875 --> 00:02:59.536
Registering subsidiary
companies left and right.

00:03:00.075 --> 00:03:02.205
Doing everything to distance
themselves from any connection.

00:03:03.515 --> 00:03:05.162
And do you know who
the major shareholder is?

00:03:05.795 --> 00:03:06.765
Who?

00:03:11.155 --> 00:03:12.325
Mr. Bowontat.

00:03:12.995 --> 00:03:14.645
The guy who sent you flowers the other day.

00:03:18.355 --> 00:03:19.525
(2025’s Hottest Young Entrepreneur)

00:03:22.513 --> 00:03:23.555
Wait a minute.

00:03:27.555 --> 00:03:30.325
Deputy Phakphum was the one
in charge of my father's case.

00:03:31.555 --> 00:03:32.845
And as for Mr. Burin,

00:03:33.435 --> 00:03:34.965
He's that corrupt capitalist scum.

00:03:38.595 --> 00:03:40.685
Where should I send a car
to pick you up tomorrow?

00:03:45.195 --> 00:03:46.205
That won't be necessary.

00:03:46.635 --> 00:03:48.205
It's more convenient if I go by myself.

00:03:50.115 --> 00:03:50.925
Are you sure?

00:03:51.635 --> 00:03:53.865
Since you’ve finally
made some time for me.

00:03:56.595 --> 00:03:58.451
It's no trouble at all.

00:03:59.235 --> 00:04:01.085
Then, I'll see you tomorrow.

00:04:01.835 --> 00:04:02.685
Bye.

00:05:38.075 --> 00:05:39.927
I have to work tonight.

00:05:40.395 --> 00:05:43.900
I’ll probably be back late.
Go to bed, don't wait up.

00:05:45.995 --> 00:05:47.205
Again?

00:05:47.715 --> 00:05:49.405
I really don't want you to be in that unit.

00:05:49.875 --> 00:05:51.765
It’s way too dangerous for a woman.

00:05:53.955 --> 00:05:57.645
Um, should I ask my dad to transfer you?

00:06:02.195 --> 00:06:03.645
I love this job.

00:06:04.675 --> 00:06:07.005
I'll never use my privileges, no matter what.

00:06:10.315 --> 00:06:11.925
We are not going to talk about this anymore.

00:06:33.675 --> 00:06:34.845
I’m sorry.

00:06:36.835 --> 00:06:38.045
I guess I’m just tired.

00:06:40.235 --> 00:06:41.485
So I was a bit too blunt.

00:06:45.395 --> 00:06:46.325
It's okay.

00:06:47.115 --> 00:06:48.887
I'm just worried about you.

00:06:48.995 --> 00:06:50.700
I see you looking stressed quite often.

00:06:52.755 --> 00:06:53.925
Um.

00:06:54.795 --> 00:06:57.429
We’ve been working non-stop,
without any breaks.

00:06:58.595 --> 00:07:00.167
How about we find some time to relax?

00:07:01.875 --> 00:07:02.685
Where should we go?

00:07:06.355 --> 00:07:07.473
Should we go abroad?

00:07:07.675 --> 00:07:08.805
For maybe four or five days.

00:07:10.035 --> 00:07:10.925
Oh.

00:07:11.475 --> 00:07:12.725
Four or five days?

00:07:14.115 --> 00:07:15.285
That might be difficult.

00:07:16.755 --> 00:07:18.045
I probably won't have the time.

00:07:20.755 --> 00:07:21.645
I figured.

00:07:23.115 --> 00:07:24.125
Then,

00:07:24.555 --> 00:07:26.522
I'll go think about.

00:07:26.595 --> 00:07:27.605
Where would be a good place to go.

00:07:28.595 --> 00:07:29.725
We don't actually have to go.

00:07:29.995 --> 00:07:30.885
Just think about it for now.

00:07:59.835 --> 00:08:01.085
I'm sorry.

00:08:03.875 --> 00:08:06.318
You deserve to be with
someone who has more time for you.

00:08:19.755 --> 00:08:21.225
I've already made my choice.

00:08:22.475 --> 00:08:24.042
Don't have to have a lot of time.

00:08:25.475 --> 00:08:26.845
As long as they're real, that's enough for me.

00:09:24.475 --> 00:09:25.525
Who are you going to see?

00:09:26.195 --> 00:09:27.125
Bowontat.

00:09:27.555 --> 00:09:29.047
Are you out of your mind, Tarn?

00:09:29.355 --> 00:09:30.965
That guy is dangerous, you know.

00:09:31.595 --> 00:09:34.016
I want to confirm
the relationship between those two.

00:09:34.395 --> 00:09:36.905
Tarn, that guy clearly looks like a junkie.

00:09:37.435 --> 00:09:39.322
As if there’s anything left
in his brain for you to find.

00:09:39.515 --> 00:09:41.725
The point is he’s dangerous.

00:09:41.955 --> 00:09:43.725
He could even be a killer.

00:09:45.675 --> 00:09:46.645
Don't worry.

00:09:47.075 --> 00:09:48.725
I’ll take care of myself.

00:09:50.595 --> 00:09:51.365
Tarn!

00:10:04.715 --> 00:10:05.885
You’re right on time, Captain.

00:10:12.315 --> 00:10:13.685
I didn't want to waste your time.

00:10:17.915 --> 00:10:19.325
You look exceptionally beautiful today.

00:10:22.275 --> 00:10:23.805
I hope you didn't bring a gun along.

00:10:27.395 --> 00:10:28.605
You can trust me.

00:10:29.795 --> 00:10:31.205
Because if I were going to shoot,

00:10:31.915 --> 00:10:33.927
The target wouldn't even see the gun coming.

00:10:36.069 --> 00:10:37.085
Are you kidding me?

00:10:39.595 --> 00:10:40.325
Just kidding.

00:10:41.115 --> 00:10:42.605
I really do like someone like you.

00:10:44.195 --> 00:10:44.925
After you.

00:10:55.955 --> 00:10:56.605
After you.

00:11:03.835 --> 00:11:06.336
When I said I liked you, I meant it.

00:11:06.875 --> 00:11:08.205
I like women who are beautiful,

00:11:10.315 --> 00:11:11.165
Smart,

00:11:13.115 --> 00:11:13.885
Fierce,

00:11:15.075 --> 00:11:15.725
Composed,

00:11:16.915 --> 00:11:17.925
And a little bit dangerous.

00:11:18.515 --> 00:11:19.445
Just like you.

00:11:22.675 --> 00:11:24.045
Um...

00:11:24.875 --> 00:11:26.005
And what about Vicky?

00:11:28.275 --> 00:11:29.325
Let's order some drinks first.

00:11:30.155 --> 00:11:30.765
Waiter.

00:11:34.755 --> 00:11:35.765
What can I get for you?

00:11:36.115 --> 00:11:37.445
I'll have the usual. One bottle.

00:11:37.795 --> 00:11:38.565
Certainly.

00:11:42.115 --> 00:11:43.325
Is this drink very strong?

00:11:43.595 --> 00:11:45.885
I’m not really looking
to get drunk right now.

00:11:47.115 --> 00:11:50.042
It's my usual. Light and easy to drink.

00:11:51.275 --> 00:11:52.045
Alright.

00:12:03.595 --> 00:12:04.525
About Vicky...

00:12:05.235 --> 00:12:06.565
I don't have any feelings for her.

00:12:08.595 --> 00:12:11.100
My father wants our families
to be united through marriage.

00:12:12.355 --> 00:12:13.645
But I’m not into arranged marriages.

00:12:15.715 --> 00:12:18.567
Plenty of women share your status.

00:12:19.035 --> 00:12:20.285
So why does it have to be Vicky?

00:12:22.315 --> 00:12:23.685
It’s not about being a good match.

00:12:24.395 --> 00:12:25.685
It’s about history.

00:12:26.195 --> 00:12:28.869
My father and Vicky’s
father used to be very close.

00:12:31.995 --> 00:12:33.245
That’s strange, though.

00:12:33.755 --> 00:12:36.629
Vicky never mentioned
being close to your family.

00:12:37.915 --> 00:12:39.125
What would Vicky know?

00:12:49.795 --> 00:12:52.405
Deputy Phakphum was the one
in charge of my father's case.

00:12:53.755 --> 00:12:57.322
And as for Mr. Burin,
He's that corrupt capitalist scum.

00:13:04.235 --> 00:13:04.885
Yes.

00:13:17.475 --> 00:13:18.965
My father is very influential.

00:13:19.315 --> 00:13:21.485
I’m on a first-name basis
with everyone at Police HQ.

00:13:22.355 --> 00:13:26.345
Didn't know Deputy
Phakphum played politics too.

00:13:30.755 --> 00:13:32.558
Is there anyone who isn’t involved in politics?

00:13:33.595 --> 00:13:35.207
Even if you don’t mess with politics,

00:13:35.355 --> 00:13:36.805
Politics will eventually
mess with you anyway.

00:13:37.115 --> 00:13:37.845
Right?

00:13:39.395 --> 00:13:39.925
Eh!

00:13:40.755 --> 00:13:42.325
But you haven't touched your drink yet.

00:13:50.835 --> 00:13:52.685
Just watching you drink makes me happy.

00:13:53.995 --> 00:13:55.565
When you’re drunk,

00:13:57.675 --> 00:13:59.205
You look quite charming.

00:14:01.555 --> 00:14:02.365
In that case...

00:14:03.395 --> 00:14:04.685
Let's have a drink together.

00:14:25.595 --> 00:14:27.205
How can I serve you today?

00:14:27.675 --> 00:14:28.085
Hey.

00:14:29.155 --> 00:14:31.885
The usual, but keep it light and fun.

00:14:32.555 --> 00:14:33.325
You got it.

00:15:31.715 --> 00:15:32.685
Can't handle it, Captain?

00:15:33.515 --> 00:15:34.725
Why don't you rest in my room for a bit?

00:15:35.035 --> 00:15:36.245
My dad’s a shareholder here anyway.

00:15:37.195 --> 00:15:39.685
I'm fine. I've already called a cab.

00:15:42.435 --> 00:15:43.805
-Ow!
-Captain!

00:15:44.475 --> 00:15:45.485
I told you, you can't handle it.

00:15:48.833 --> 00:15:50.325
You’re in no shape to go anywhere, Captain.

00:15:50.715 --> 00:15:52.045
Go stay in my room for now.

00:15:52.835 --> 00:15:53.245
Let me go!

00:15:54.115 --> 00:15:54.885
Let me go!

00:15:55.235 --> 00:15:55.725
Hey.

00:16:01.235 --> 00:16:02.165
Who the hell are you?

00:16:02.915 --> 00:16:04.125
What the hell are you doing meddling in this?

00:16:04.195 --> 00:16:04.845
You want a piece of me?

00:16:04.995 --> 00:16:05.725
Hey!

00:16:08.795 --> 00:16:09.645
What's going on here?

00:16:27.635 --> 00:16:28.405
Get in the car!

00:16:42.515 --> 00:16:44.405
I must apologize for my son's behavior.

00:16:45.675 --> 00:16:47.605
He’s usually not this inappropriate.

00:16:48.395 --> 00:16:52.005
I don't know what got
into him to make him act so rude.

00:16:52.635 --> 00:16:54.325
He didn't just cross the line of manners.

00:16:54.955 --> 00:16:56.525
But he also harassed my friend.

00:16:58.115 --> 00:17:02.685
Next time, you and his
handlers better watch him.

00:17:13.355 --> 00:17:15.045
The two of us will be taking our leave now.

00:17:24.275 --> 00:17:25.085
About Vicky...

00:17:25.875 --> 00:17:27.165
I don't have any feelings for her.

00:17:27.595 --> 00:17:29.885
My father just wants our
families to be joined by marriage.

00:17:38.555 --> 00:17:40.645
Go find out who these two really are.

00:17:41.675 --> 00:17:42.685
Yes, sir.

00:17:47.275 --> 00:17:49.965
You sure you don't need a hospital, Tarn?

00:17:51.675 --> 00:17:52.525
Nah.

00:17:53.235 --> 00:17:54.325
I'm good.

00:17:56.155 --> 00:17:57.205
Sigh.

00:17:58.955 --> 00:17:59.645
I...

00:18:00.235 --> 00:18:02.125
kept an eye on it the whole time.

00:18:02.875 --> 00:18:05.085
And I only had a tiny sip.

00:18:06.595 --> 00:18:07.605
Oh man.

00:18:10.035 --> 00:18:12.685
It's their turf.
They’ve got a whole system going.

00:18:15.235 --> 00:18:16.645
I’m heading into Vicky’s house now.

00:18:29.795 --> 00:18:30.565
Tarn.

00:18:31.755 --> 00:18:32.525
I'm good.

00:18:32.755 --> 00:18:33.445
You sure about that?

00:18:38.555 --> 00:18:39.605
What happened?

00:18:42.195 --> 00:18:43.685
You look terrible.

00:18:46.315 --> 00:18:47.845
Just had a few drinks.

00:18:48.355 --> 00:18:50.645
But I'm totally fine.

00:18:53.195 --> 00:18:56.096
I had no idea tonight’s field work was at a club.

00:18:58.315 --> 00:19:01.011
Why? Would you have tagged along if you knew?

00:19:01.995 --> 00:19:06.085
Yep. General Vicky will take
over and look after Captain Tarn.

00:19:08.115 --> 00:19:09.405
Thanks, Captain Pete.

00:19:10.195 --> 00:19:12.205
I'll take it from here.

00:19:12.875 --> 00:19:15.767
Sure. Call me anytime if you need anything.

00:19:16.675 --> 00:19:17.405
Yes.

00:19:21.355 --> 00:19:22.125
Step.

00:19:22.835 --> 00:19:23.485
Pete.

00:19:24.675 --> 00:19:26.405
-Get home safe.
-I'll get the door.

00:19:27.235 --> 00:19:28.125
Bye bye.

00:19:36.155 --> 00:19:38.869
Sleep in my room tonight. I’ll take care of you.

00:19:41.195 --> 00:19:42.805
Are you hiding something from me?

00:19:44.635 --> 00:19:45.365
Hmm?

00:19:48.435 --> 00:19:49.085
I...

00:19:49.435 --> 00:19:50.805
I’ve been drugged.

00:19:52.435 --> 00:19:53.125
Drugged?

00:19:53.715 --> 00:19:54.605
With what?

00:19:59.755 --> 00:20:01.565
What kind of drug?

00:20:02.395 --> 00:20:03.645
Don’t panic.

00:20:04.835 --> 00:20:06.045
I’m okay now.

00:20:07.035 --> 00:20:08.645
How are you okay? Just look at you.

00:20:11.755 --> 00:20:12.565
What was it?

00:20:26.835 --> 00:20:29.245
Look, I think you should go to bed.

00:20:33.115 --> 00:20:35.125
Right now, I just want to be close to you.

00:21:57.075 --> 00:21:58.485
Is this the drug talking?

00:22:16.795 --> 00:22:18.045
It’s not because of the drug.

00:22:21.195 --> 00:22:22.205
It’s because of you.

00:22:34.075 --> 00:22:35.365
You are the first.

00:22:37.195 --> 00:22:38.005
And the only one.

00:25:33.835 --> 00:25:35.325
Is this the drug talking?

00:25:36.235 --> 00:25:37.485
It’s not because of the drug.

00:25:40.635 --> 00:25:41.565
It’s because of you.

00:25:43.355 --> 00:25:44.485
You are the first.

00:25:46.395 --> 00:25:47.405
And the only one.

00:26:21.435 --> 00:26:22.325
What’s wrong?

00:26:23.515 --> 00:26:24.445
What are you thinking about?

00:26:32.035 --> 00:26:33.285
About last night

00:26:35.235 --> 00:26:37.085
Was it real, or just the drug talking?

00:26:41.555 --> 00:26:42.365
Well...

00:26:43.915 --> 00:26:45.885
Then listen to me again now that I'm sober.

00:26:47.475 --> 00:26:49.445
So I can prove that I truly want you.

00:27:49.595 --> 00:27:51.393
I'm at a disadvantage here.

00:27:52.955 --> 00:27:54.620
It's only 6 AM.

00:27:55.835 --> 00:27:57.165
We still have plenty of time.

00:28:04.875 --> 00:28:05.685
Right?

00:28:06.715 --> 00:28:07.765
So you know.

00:28:08.515 --> 00:28:11.296
What it's like to do this
when I'm 100% conscious.

00:28:22.355 --> 00:28:24.149
I'm not letting you get the upper hand.

00:28:30.595 --> 00:28:31.365
What are you doing?

00:28:33.755 --> 00:28:34.685
I'm pinning you down.

00:28:36.635 --> 00:28:37.829
But I'm a police.

00:28:42.195 --> 00:28:43.553
And do you want to be caught?

00:30:01.875 --> 00:30:03.545
You still kept this photo?

00:30:05.115 --> 00:30:05.765
What?

00:30:11.795 --> 00:30:13.447
This photo looks really old.

00:30:18.355 --> 00:30:20.665
It's from my childhood birthday party.

00:30:21.155 --> 00:30:22.925
The other girl is P'Looknam.

00:30:23.515 --> 00:30:25.525
She was like a sweet older sister to me.

00:30:30.035 --> 00:30:31.687
And where is she now?

00:30:36.315 --> 00:30:37.962
I have no idea.

00:30:38.595 --> 00:30:40.205
We only knew each other for a short time.

00:30:40.675 --> 00:30:42.285
Then suddenly, she just disappeared.

00:30:42.675 --> 00:30:46.940
When I asked my dad to look for her,
he told me she had already moved away.

00:30:54.195 --> 00:30:56.158
It seems like you really cared about her.

00:31:01.595 --> 00:31:05.118
I’m an only child,
so I’ve always been lonely.

00:31:06.475 --> 00:31:08.451
After meeting her.

00:31:08.995 --> 00:31:10.405
It was like finally having a big sister.

00:31:10.955 --> 00:31:12.442
And my very first best friend.

00:31:15.475 --> 00:31:18.256
Daddy, hurry up! I’m going to be late for school.

00:31:18.995 --> 00:31:20.885
Looknam, I can't keep up with you.

00:31:21.607 --> 00:31:22.845
P'Looknam.

00:31:23.875 --> 00:31:24.925
Nong Noo.

00:31:25.355 --> 00:31:28.365
Um, Looknam just wanted
to give a letter to Nong Noo.

00:31:28.435 --> 00:31:29.445
Oh, is that so?

00:31:33.355 --> 00:31:34.125
Wow!

00:31:34.675 --> 00:31:37.776
Nong Noo got a letter
just like the toad in the fairy tale!

00:31:40.155 --> 00:31:42.205
So, my daughter has turned into a toad now?

00:31:43.115 --> 00:31:44.685
Yes! I’m a toad.

00:31:51.235 --> 00:31:52.005
I'm a little Frog.

00:31:52.475 --> 00:31:53.525
Little Toad.

00:32:06.395 --> 00:32:08.478
Yay! We're here.

00:32:22.955 --> 00:32:24.896
What is this?

00:32:26.155 --> 00:32:28.496
This is a crown for a princess, Your Highness.

00:32:41.155 --> 00:32:43.073
But after my mom passed away.

00:32:43.515 --> 00:32:45.045
This house became so quiet.

00:32:46.275 --> 00:32:48.371
It makes me miss her even more.

00:32:49.275 --> 00:32:50.565
And I miss P'Looknam too.

00:32:56.155 --> 00:32:58.389
I’m still waiting for her second letter.

00:33:00.075 --> 00:33:01.936
She said she would send one.

00:33:03.635 --> 00:33:07.100
But... I’ve never received it, even to this day.

00:33:48.235 --> 00:33:51.171
What are you doing? Why aren't you helping me pack?

00:33:52.035 --> 00:33:53.725
I'm writing a letter to Nong Noo.

00:33:58.955 --> 00:34:00.245
-No, you can't.
-Mom.

00:34:00.435 --> 00:34:02.725
I won't tell her where we're going.

00:34:02.755 --> 00:34:04.205
Absolutely not.

00:34:04.435 --> 00:34:07.536
-Mom.
-We’re leaving quietly without letting anyone know.

00:34:08.035 --> 00:34:09.660
Especially that family.

00:34:11.955 --> 00:34:13.205
Mom.

00:34:13.795 --> 00:34:15.245
Mom.

00:34:15.275 --> 00:34:17.245
Mom.

00:34:19.595 --> 00:34:20.245
Go.

00:34:21.155 --> 00:34:23.776
Hurry up and help me pack your
clothes. We’re running out of time!

00:34:23.835 --> 00:34:25.285
- Mom.
- Here.

00:34:25.915 --> 00:34:28.285
Put these in the bag.
I’ll go grab some more.

00:35:22.475 --> 00:35:25.242
- Let’s go, P'Looknam.
- Class is about to start.

00:36:26.235 --> 00:36:27.645
- Everyone ready?
- Ready.

00:36:28.195 --> 00:36:28.885
Go.

00:36:36.075 --> 00:36:36.845
Move!

00:36:37.635 --> 00:36:39.165
What’s going on? You can’t go in there!

00:36:39.195 --> 00:36:40.096
Search warrant!

00:36:40.835 --> 00:36:41.765
Search every inch!

00:36:42.075 --> 00:36:43.725
Don’t let a single one get away.

00:36:45.075 --> 00:36:45.645
Hey.

00:36:46.195 --> 00:36:46.885
Don't run!

00:36:48.075 --> 00:36:48.949
Don't resist!

00:36:49.155 --> 00:36:50.045
Check everything.

00:36:50.395 --> 00:36:51.965
- Don't move.
- Don't let them escape.

00:36:52.795 --> 00:36:54.085
Check under the seats.

00:37:11.275 --> 00:37:12.285
Step back.

00:37:14.915 --> 00:37:15.925
Step back.

00:37:18.355 --> 00:37:19.405
There’s nothing here.

00:38:21.315 --> 00:38:22.645
The other room is clear, Captain.

00:38:23.595 --> 00:38:24.965
- Fan out and search!
- Yes, sir.

00:39:13.755 --> 00:39:15.205
Notify Forensics.

00:39:15.235 --> 00:39:17.085
Requesting Forensics at the scene. Over.

00:39:27.275 --> 00:39:29.936
Reporting live from the scene.

00:39:29.955 --> 00:39:34.325
- Following a police raid Bangkok luxury club.
- Who is it?

00:39:35.055 --> 00:39:38.220
By officers from the Special Crime units.

00:39:38.355 --> 00:39:43.845
They raided this luxury club
and discovered various types of narcotics.

00:39:44.355 --> 00:39:46.405
But the most shocking discovery.

00:39:46.795 --> 00:39:55.525
The discovery of a slaughter room
linked to multiple sexual assault complaints.

00:39:56.875 --> 00:40:00.525
VIP guests are reportedly the perpetrators.

00:40:00.675 --> 00:40:09.438
Staff allegedly aided in
drugging and moving victims to the room.

00:40:09.835 --> 00:40:17.509
A hat and blood-stained clothing
were discovered in a hidden room.

00:40:17.635 --> 00:40:20.165
Everything was found
carefully wrapped in plastic.

00:40:20.475 --> 00:40:24.185
It is suspected there was
an attempt to destroy the evidence.

00:40:24.595 --> 00:40:32.193
Initially, all evidence sent
for forensic DNA identification.

00:40:32.435 --> 00:40:43.145
Pending DNA results, suspect faces
multiple charges from bodily harm to homicide.

00:40:57.155 --> 00:41:00.205
The police raided our club!
Do you even know that yet? Huh?

00:41:01.355 --> 00:41:02.525
How is that possible, Pa?

00:41:06.435 --> 00:41:08.700
You’ve brought a war to our
doorstep, you piece of shit!

00:41:09.995 --> 00:41:12.442
Out of thousands, tens of thousands of women.

00:41:12.715 --> 00:41:14.325
You just had to go and drug a cop!

00:41:14.875 --> 00:41:18.045
I thought having her as
my woman would make things easier, Pa.

00:41:18.635 --> 00:41:20.700
What part of your
brain did you use to think that?

00:41:21.155 --> 00:41:24.025
Or is it because I let the maid
raise you since the day you were born?

00:41:24.315 --> 00:41:26.531
Did she shake you too hard
that it made you this stupid?

00:41:29.915 --> 00:41:31.005
Now, you listen to me.

00:41:32.155 --> 00:41:33.205
From now on.

00:41:33.835 --> 00:41:35.393
Unless I give the order.

00:41:36.195 --> 00:41:37.365
You don't do a damn thing!

00:41:50.035 --> 00:41:50.805
Hello.

00:41:51.475 --> 00:41:54.285
Hello, Commander Praken.

00:41:54.515 --> 00:41:56.605
This is Minister Burin speaking.

00:41:57.555 --> 00:41:59.165
Good day, Minister.

00:41:59.755 --> 00:42:01.005
How may I be of service, sir?

00:42:01.995 --> 00:42:04.045
I won't beat around the bush.

00:42:04.955 --> 00:42:07.445
About that hat and the clothing in that room.

00:42:07.675 --> 00:42:09.045
Dispose of them for me.

00:42:09.715 --> 00:42:13.245
As for the rest, just proceed as usual.

00:42:14.078 --> 00:42:16.965
Just name your price, Commander.

00:42:17.435 --> 00:42:18.725
I won't object.

00:42:21.675 --> 00:42:23.045
I'm afraid I must apologize.

00:42:23.995 --> 00:42:25.965
But this is a major case.

00:42:26.875 --> 00:42:30.125
Both local and international media are all over it.

00:42:32.515 --> 00:42:34.905
I want you to think this
through carefully, Commander.

00:42:36.555 --> 00:42:38.085
There is nothing to think about.

00:42:38.675 --> 00:42:42.445
I am simply doing my duty and what is right.

00:42:43.555 --> 00:42:44.805
Arrogant prick!

00:42:45.475 --> 00:42:46.485
Let me tell you something.

00:42:46.795 --> 00:42:49.367
I’ve taken down people much bigger than you.

00:42:58.435 --> 00:43:00.205
You guys are staring so hard.

00:43:00.795 --> 00:43:02.780
Why don't I just put it on speaker then?

00:43:06.115 --> 00:43:09.109
And if I’m not mistaken,
was that the Big Boss calling?

00:43:10.115 --> 00:43:10.805
Yep.

00:43:11.515 --> 00:43:14.485
And let me guess he called to offer a bribe.

00:43:16.155 --> 00:43:16.965
Exactly.

00:43:17.675 --> 00:43:18.445
Whoa.

00:43:19.115 --> 00:43:20.525
We should have recorded that.

00:43:23.435 --> 00:43:25.485
I won't beat around the bush.

00:43:26.395 --> 00:43:29.189
About that hat and the clothing in that room.

00:43:29.435 --> 00:43:30.845
Dispose of them for me.

00:43:37.195 --> 00:43:37.965
Back to work.

00:43:39.435 --> 00:43:40.205
Great.

00:43:48.635 --> 00:43:49.725
How did it go, Pa?

00:43:56.195 --> 00:43:57.045
What?

00:43:57.515 --> 00:43:59.405
I have some new information
you should be aware of, sir.

00:43:59.835 --> 00:44:03.322
Tara is the daughter of that
stubborn activist leader from 19 years ago

00:44:06.475 --> 00:44:09.891
Tara is that stubborn leader's daughter?

00:44:11.035 --> 00:44:12.525
Does Phakphum know yet?

00:44:13.091 --> 00:44:13.805
Not yet, sir.

00:44:16.195 --> 00:44:18.745
She's getting close to
Phakphum and his daughter.

00:44:19.395 --> 00:44:20.525
All for the sake of revenge.

00:44:21.675 --> 00:44:22.885
That seems to be the case, sir.

00:44:25.115 --> 00:44:27.205
Then let her deal with Phakphum first.

00:44:27.835 --> 00:44:29.725
We'll take care of her later.

00:44:29.995 --> 00:44:31.525
A woman all by herself.

00:44:32.475 --> 00:44:33.445
Won't be a problem.

00:44:35.475 --> 00:44:37.045
What did you do to Captain Tarn?

00:44:40.035 --> 00:44:41.325
I buried her, that's what!

00:44:42.715 --> 00:44:44.045
Did you really have to go that far?

00:44:45.555 --> 00:44:47.085
You’re still worried about her?

00:44:48.315 --> 00:44:50.245
That woman couldn't care less about you.

00:44:52.235 --> 00:44:54.165
She’s with Vicky

00:44:55.115 --> 00:44:56.685
Can’t you see that?

00:45:00.925 --> 00:45:03.722
Some staff members were in on it, too.

00:45:03.875 --> 00:45:06.798
All I heard was that the drinks were spiked.

00:45:06.915 --> 00:45:07.805
Who is this person?

00:45:12.555 --> 00:45:15.965
I can’t believe
that Captain Tarn, while on duty

00:45:16.435 --> 00:45:18.985
could be this cool.

00:45:24.955 --> 00:45:29.305
I finally get why Mali is such
a die-hard fan of the Captain.

00:45:32.115 --> 00:45:36.300
Oh, I just thought
of a great place for our trip.

00:45:37.835 --> 00:45:38.685
Where to?

00:45:42.315 --> 00:45:45.118
I’ve already discussed it all with my dad.

00:45:46.115 --> 00:45:47.162
Shall we head out now?

00:45:50.275 --> 00:45:52.042
He’s been gone for quite a while.

00:45:52.795 --> 00:45:55.056
Nothing's wrong, right?

00:45:56.115 --> 00:45:58.051
Dad just finished his meeting.

00:45:58.355 --> 00:46:01.047
He said he wants to rest a bit longer.

00:46:01.395 --> 00:46:03.989
It seems like he's been under a lot
of stress lately with no breaks at all.

00:46:07.675 --> 00:46:10.300
See? We should take a break too.

00:46:20.875 --> 00:46:22.220
So, anyway.

00:46:23.475 --> 00:46:24.805
Where exactly are we going?

00:46:39.795 --> 00:46:41.278
Check the list thoroughly.

00:46:41.595 --> 00:46:43.725
Don't let anything slip.
Make sure they match.

00:46:56.715 --> 00:46:57.325
Sir.

00:46:58.318 --> 00:46:59.045
Yes.

00:47:00.256 --> 00:47:01.565
Cut the formalities.

00:47:03.075 --> 00:47:04.765
I have something I need your urgent help with.

00:47:06.475 --> 00:47:07.965
And it has to be only you guys.

00:47:18.915 --> 00:47:20.845
This is my mother’s old house.

00:47:21.355 --> 00:47:23.651
In the past, the three
of us loved coming here.

00:47:23.955 --> 00:47:27.005
Since Mom passed,
Dad hasn't been back.

00:47:27.515 --> 00:47:30.620
He said being here makes him
miss her so much it’s unbearable.

00:47:30.915 --> 00:47:32.725
He hates seeing himself
in a vulnerable state.

00:47:36.955 --> 00:47:37.885
Shall we take a look inside?

00:47:52.675 --> 00:47:54.045
- After you.
- Thank you.

00:47:57.955 --> 00:47:58.925
Whoa.

00:48:01.435 --> 00:48:02.685
This house is so lovely.

00:48:03.795 --> 00:48:05.365
It looks like someone lives here all the time.

00:48:06.355 --> 00:48:07.165
People do live here.

00:48:07.555 --> 00:48:09.365
There’s a gardener and a maid here around.

00:48:09.595 --> 00:48:14.325
My father insisted that everything
stay exactly as it was when Mom was alive.

00:48:14.795 --> 00:48:18.140
Maintenance is fine, but moving
anything is strictly forbidden.

00:48:32.475 --> 00:48:33.645
What’s on your mind?

00:48:39.515 --> 00:48:40.805
Just feeling like...

00:48:46.395 --> 00:48:47.485
I'm hungry.

00:48:50.635 --> 00:48:52.593
Sure. What do you want? I'll cook for you.

00:48:52.915 --> 00:48:53.925
- Really?
- Um.

00:48:54.595 --> 00:48:56.176
- Let's grab our stuff first.
- Let's grab our stuff first.

00:49:02.442 --> 00:49:03.925
What are you in the mood for today?

00:49:04.635 --> 00:49:06.176
I'll eat whatever you make.

00:49:51.035 --> 00:49:52.245
The veggies are here.

00:49:55.555 --> 00:49:58.167
You can go take a break.
I'll handle the rest.

00:50:00.515 --> 00:50:03.125
I'll go put the stuff
in the bedroom for you.

00:50:03.755 --> 00:50:05.165
Ok, Thank you.

00:50:05.915 --> 00:50:06.965
Be careful.

00:51:43.315 --> 00:51:44.925
Hello.

00:51:50.275 --> 00:51:51.325
What are you looking at?

00:51:51.515 --> 00:51:55.965
Oh, I just found this album.

00:51:59.155 --> 00:52:03.162
It’s my family album.
My mom took so many photos.

00:52:03.875 --> 00:52:06.158
- Want to take a look?
- Sure.

00:52:11.035 --> 00:52:12.445
Okay.

00:52:13.115 --> 00:52:14.105
There are so many of them.

00:52:16.995 --> 00:52:18.478
Here she is P'Looknam.

00:52:18.595 --> 00:52:19.765
The one I told you about.

00:52:20.235 --> 00:52:22.229
Our families used to be very close.

00:52:22.675 --> 00:52:25.918
My parents and P'Looknam’s parents.

00:52:40.595 --> 00:52:42.718
The memories are
still as beautiful as ever.

00:52:44.315 --> 00:52:47.885
It’s a shame...that
the reality wasn't like that at all.

00:52:53.755 --> 00:52:56.985
Sorry, I shouldn't have brought that up.

00:52:58.035 --> 00:52:58.885
Hey.

00:52:59.435 --> 00:53:01.205
Is the food ready yet?

00:53:01.515 --> 00:53:02.365
It’s all done.

00:53:03.155 --> 00:53:04.045
Let's go eat.

00:53:04.235 --> 00:53:05.205
- Let's go.
- Go.

00:53:05.235 --> 00:53:05.765
- Go.
- Go.

00:53:05.795 --> 00:53:07.125
- I'm starving.
- Come on

00:53:08.976 --> 00:53:10.205
Let's go.

00:53:32.715 --> 00:53:34.245
You may go and rest now, sir.

00:53:34.435 --> 00:53:36.525
I'll handle the rest of the information myself.

00:53:36.875 --> 00:53:37.525
Um.

00:53:44.816 --> 00:53:45.765
Hey!

00:53:50.195 --> 00:53:51.845
Don't make this difficult for us, sir.

00:53:52.235 --> 00:53:54.125
Mr. Burin just wants to
invite you for a little gathering.

00:54:24.955 --> 00:54:28.445
My apologies for having
my men bring you here like this.

00:54:29.475 --> 00:54:31.527
Well, you wouldn't
pick up any of my calls, Deputy.

00:54:33.515 --> 00:54:35.731
Why did you hand
over the evidence to them?

00:54:37.195 --> 00:54:40.125
Or do you already
know who Captain Tara really is?

00:54:42.715 --> 00:54:44.833
Does it look appetizing? I made it myself

00:54:45.555 --> 00:54:47.073
The absolute best.

00:54:47.135 --> 00:54:49.287
Try this.

00:54:50.195 --> 00:54:51.685
I think you'll like it.

00:54:55.595 --> 00:54:56.165
Is it good?

00:54:57.795 --> 00:54:58.725
It’s delicious

00:55:01.995 --> 00:55:02.445
Hey.

00:55:03.195 --> 00:55:06.585
Tell me about your childhood.
You’ve put it off so many times now.

00:55:07.595 --> 00:55:08.645
Please.

00:55:09.275 --> 00:55:11.296
Just tell me.

00:55:13.195 --> 00:55:13.885
Alright, fine.

00:55:19.915 --> 00:55:21.838
I’m an only child.

00:55:22.515 --> 00:55:24.442
My mom is in the States now.

00:55:25.555 --> 00:55:26.685
As for...

00:55:28.395 --> 00:55:30.442
My dad passed away when I was ten.

00:55:35.315 --> 00:55:37.047
When I was twelve.

00:55:37.515 --> 00:55:40.487
My mom got a job there,
so she moved over there as well.

00:55:41.995 --> 00:55:43.927
She left me with my aunt for a while.

00:55:44.795 --> 00:55:45.885
Mom said that.

00:55:46.555 --> 00:55:48.085
Once she gets settled.

00:55:48.995 --> 00:55:50.445
She would take me with her.

00:55:53.915 --> 00:55:56.771
But when the time came,
I didn't really want to go.

00:55:59.555 --> 00:56:00.825
Why is that?

00:56:06.675 --> 00:56:07.971
Because if I left,

00:56:10.555 --> 00:56:13.260
I was afraid I’d forget
what happened here.

00:56:19.395 --> 00:56:21.500
We actually have a lot in common.

00:56:24.475 --> 00:56:25.945
I’m starting to understand now.

00:56:26.995 --> 00:56:30.433
Why the two of us
clicked right from the start.

00:56:38.635 --> 00:56:40.362
It must be...

00:56:41.595 --> 00:56:42.931
Fate.

00:56:54.835 --> 00:56:56.051
It’s my dad calling.

00:56:58.475 --> 00:56:59.856
Yes, Dad?

00:57:00.995 --> 00:57:02.525
Don't panic, Vicky.

00:57:03.515 --> 00:57:05.285
Your father is having dinner with me.

00:57:06.395 --> 00:57:08.085
So, I’m just borrowing his phone.

00:57:09.075 --> 00:57:12.176
And I know you’re with Captain Tara.

00:57:12.915 --> 00:57:14.165
Let me speak with her.

00:57:19.115 --> 00:57:21.909
Minister Burin.
He wants to speak with you.

00:57:39.155 --> 00:57:40.005
Hello.

00:57:40.155 --> 00:57:42.645
Hello, Captain.
I won't beat around the bush.

00:57:43.715 --> 00:57:45.882
Hand over everything you found to me."

00:57:46.515 --> 00:57:48.965
If you don't want Phakphum to end up dead.

00:57:56.155 --> 00:57:57.645
And why should I care?

00:57:58.202 --> 00:57:59.565
You guys are on the same side.

00:58:02.675 --> 00:58:03.962
What same side?

00:58:06.675 --> 00:58:07.669
Don't come.

00:58:08.555 --> 00:58:09.565
Don't come, Tara.

00:58:09.875 --> 00:58:11.285
Don't tell Vicky anything.

00:58:12.115 --> 00:58:14.202
Take all this evidence to your boss.

00:58:15.715 --> 00:58:16.325
Dad.

00:58:16.955 --> 00:58:17.925
I heard my father's voice.

00:58:18.155 --> 00:58:18.925
You!

00:58:21.595 --> 00:58:24.245
Don’t you want to know how your father really died?

00:58:24.755 --> 00:58:26.665
If you want to know, bring the items to me.

00:58:27.395 --> 00:58:29.980
Because if Phakphum dies by my hand.

00:58:30.835 --> 00:58:32.896
You won't get your revenge.

00:58:38.035 --> 00:58:41.233
Wait! Dad? Dad, where are you? Dad!

00:58:41.435 --> 00:58:43.607
Don't you dare touch my father!

00:59:13.315 --> 00:59:14.085
Revenge?

00:59:16.275 --> 00:59:17.045
What is this all about?

00:59:20.275 --> 00:59:21.045
Huh?

00:59:22.755 --> 00:59:23.525
You.

00:59:24.515 --> 00:59:25.645
What is he talking about?

00:59:26.075 --> 00:59:27.285
Then where is my dad? Where is he?

00:59:27.555 --> 00:59:29.580
Huh? Where is my dad?

00:59:30.515 --> 00:59:32.913
And what is he going to do to my dad? Huh?

00:59:33.675 --> 00:59:35.927
Tell me!

00:59:36.555 --> 00:59:38.085
Huh? Where is my dad?

00:59:38.235 --> 00:59:39.565
Where is my dad?

00:59:40.115 --> 00:59:41.205
Where is my dad?

00:59:41.355 --> 00:59:44.629
What is he going to do to my dad?
Huh? What is he going to do to him.

00:59:45.515 --> 00:59:48.336
Tell me! What do you know? Just tell me!

00:59:49.595 --> 00:59:50.565
You.

00:59:50.995 --> 00:59:51.765
Huh?

00:59:54.075 --> 00:59:57.536
Revenge for what? What items? Huh?

01:00:02.807 --> 01:00:04.125
What else?

01:00:04.371 --> 01:00:06.445
What else don't I know about you yet?

01:00:12.555 --> 01:00:14.398
If you hadn't played hard to get that night.

01:00:14.675 --> 01:00:17.565
You could've been
the lady of this house by now.

01:00:17.875 --> 01:00:20.365
The Captain only knows
that her father fell to his death.

01:00:20.875 --> 01:00:23.945
But you have no idea
what actually happened?

